<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-10-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="907" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d907">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 853.00/85.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Gage</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Lisbon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-10-06"><hi rend="italic">October 6,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Since October 5, 5 p.m., city unusually quiet. People apprehensive but
                            orderly. Provisional government is in charge of foreign office and all
                            national offices in Lisbon. King and royal family fled last night aboard
                            the royal yacht.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gage.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>